hard this is but listen,

1026
00:51:08,450 --> 00:51:10,780
we're both going through it. (sighs)

1027
00:51:10,780 --> 00:51:14,160
I'm trying to do the best I
can, I need you to help me.

1028
00:51:14,160 --> 00:51:17,100
Please, will you help me, please?

1029
00:51:17,100 --> 00:51:17,933
Come on.

1030
00:51:23,100 --> 00:51:25,433
Hi Murray, it's Elisa, is Bess there?

1031
00:51:26,890 --> 00:51:27,890
(intercom chatters)
She...

1032
00:51:29,060 --> 00:51:32,020
Oh no, no, well she was with me, yeah.

1033
00:51:32,020 --> 00:51:35,983
Um, oh gee, Mur, I don't have
a watch, I don't know when.

1034
00:51:37,220 --> 00:51:38,730
Well she'll be there soon, I'm sure.

1035
00:51:38,730 --> 00:51:41,530
I mean, (stammers) she should
be there any minute, yeah.

1036
00:51:42,730 --> 00:51:44,320
Listen, Sam's here, I've gotta go.

1037
00:51:44,320 --> 00:51:46,993
I'll uh, I'll call her,
I'll call her later, huh?

1038
00:51:46,993 --> 00:51:48,250
Just tell her I can't go to work tomorrow.

1039
00:51:48,250 --> 00:51:49,623
I'll, I'll explain later.

1040
00:51:50,651 --> 00:51:51,812
- So, how's Janet?

1041
00:51:51,812 --> 00:51:53,260
- (sighs) In and out of consciousness,

1042
00:51:53,260 --> 00:51:55,344
with a lot of tubes and...

1043
00:51:55,344 --> 00:51:56,177
(Sam sighs)

1044
00:51:56,177 --> 00:51:58,000
She called your name a couple of times.

1045
00:51:58,902 --> 00:52:00,102
- (sighs) How you doin'?

1046
00:52:01,090 --> 00:52:02,040
- I've been better.

1047
00:52:09,990 --> 00:52:12,540
(Elisa sighs)

1048
00:52:12,540 --> 00:52:16,806
So, Bess told Murray that
she was out with me tonight.

1049
00:52:16,806 --> 00:52:18,004
- Hm, was she?
(sighs tensely)

1050
00:52:18,004 --> 00:52:18,837
- No.

1051
00:52:21,057 --> 00:52:23,057
But I have a good idea of where she was.

1052
00:52:27,430 --> 00:52:28,493
- It's Nell Bergen.

1053
00:52:29,540 --> 00:52:31,590
It's the architect that I'm working with.

1054
00:52:32,953 --> 00:52:35,953
(employees chatter)

1055
00:52:37,270 --> 00:52:39,170
- Well, I didn't think it was Phyllis.

1056
00:52:41,941 --> 00:52:44,923
(sighs) You're living in a tent?

1057
00:52:47,889 --> 00:52:48,722
- Ah.

1058
00:52:50,071 --> 00:52:52,433
No, she has a place
downtown, I'm staying there.

1059
00:53:01,730 --> 00:53:02,563
Hi, Zo.

1060
00:53:04,704 --> 00:53:05,537
- Hi.

1061
00:53:07,415 --> 00:53:08,415
- Hi, honey.

1062
00:53:10,215 --> 00:53:11,823
- (clears throat) So, how's Zack?

1063
00:53:13,640 --> 00:53:14,473
- Fine.

1064
00:53:17,270 --> 00:53:21,440
Um, Mom, I'm gonna go
back in and sit with Gran.

1065
00:53:21,440 --> 00:53:22,280
- Okay, sweetheart.

1066
00:53:22,280 --> 00:53:25,383
I'm gonna visit with your,
with your father for a while.

1067
00:53:31,163 --> 00:53:36,163
(siren wails)
(intercom chatters)

1068
00:53:38,403 --> 00:53:40,550
- Want some more coffee?

1069
00:53:40,550 --> 00:53:41,383
- Yeah.

1070
00:53:48,020 --> 00:53:50,720
Maybe after a while, people
just have to switch roles.

1071
00:53:54,618 --> 00:53:57,020
(sighs) After being taken
care of for so long,

1072
00:53:57,020 --> 00:53:59,013
maybe you need to take care of somebody.

1073
00:54:10,048 --> 00:54:13,111
(thoughtful music)

1074
00:54:13,111 --> 00:54:15,528
(door slams)

1075
00:54:25,320 --> 00:54:26,153
- David!

1076
00:54:27,497 --> 00:54:29,278
I don't suppose that coffee's for me, huh?

1077
00:54:29,278 --> 00:54:31,383
- 'Fraid not, Nell was too tired to sleep.

1078
00:54:32,570 --> 00:54:33,730
She called a little before three

1079
00:54:33,730 --> 00:54:35,070
and said she thought
it would be a good idea

1080
00:54:35,070 --> 00:54:37,453
if she worked, but she
didn't wanna work alone.

1081
00:54:38,584 --> 00:54:42,537
- Yeah, you're a good friend, David.

1082
00:54:42,537 --> 00:54:44,713
- It's easy, I love her.

1083
00:54:45,860 --> 00:54:47,823
- Yeah, me too.

1084
00:54:50,600 --> 00:54:53,610
- David, these plans stink!

1085
00:54:53,610 --> 00:54:55,863
Please don't hurry just because I am sick.

1086
00:55:03,320 --> 00:55:04,520
How's the mother-in-law?

1087
00:55:05,583 --> 00:55:07,890
- Ah, she's out of the woods, thanks.

1088
00:55:07,890 --> 00:55:08,723
- Good.

1089
00:55:09,860 --> 00:55:11,710
Well, at least she's not gonna croak.

1090
00:55:13,116 --> 00:55:14,699
- Nell, you look...

1091
00:55:15,782 --> 00:55:16,770
You look tired.

1092
00:55:16,770 --> 00:55:17,833
- Is that compared to
people in intensive care,

1093
00:55:17,833 --> 00:55:19,713
or just dying people in general?

1094
00:55:21,060 --> 00:55:23,010
- I just remembered something I forgot.

1095
00:55:29,310 --> 00:55:31,940
- They say dying is easy, comedy's hard.

1096
00:55:31,940 --> 00:55:33,630
Boy, are they wrong.

1097
00:55:33,630 --> 00:55:36,060
Can't forget about it for one second!

1098
00:55:36,060 --> 00:55:38,250
It's this horrible
coincidental phenomena crap

1099
00:55:38,250 --> 00:55:40,950
where everywhere you turn,
there's a song on the radio.

1100
00:55:40,950 --> 00:55:42,210
There's a report about death and dying

1101
00:55:42,210 --> 00:55:43,220
on the six o'clock news.

1102
00:55:43,220 --> 00:55:46,110
There are bookstores packed
with books, just about dying!

1103
00:55:46,110 --> 00:55:48,940
There are how-to books,
because they figure no one,

1104
00:55:48,940 --> 00:55:50,940
no one gets beyond the amateur standing.

1105
00:55:53,021 --> 00:55:54,700
- (clears throat) Nell,
why don't you just go home?

1106
00:55:54,700 --> 00:55:56,970
- Because I don't want to go home!

1107
00:55:56,970 --> 00:55:58,780
So I can have some soup and listen

1108
00:55:58,780 --> 00:56:00,270
to a tape of whales giving birth.

1109
00:56:00,270 --> 00:56:02,370
Oh, that would really make me feel better!

1110
00:56:03,510 --> 00:56:05,210
Sam, why don't you leave me alone?

1111
00:56:06,130 --> 00:56:08,120
- Is this about me
seeing Elisa last night?

1112
00:56:08,120 --> 00:56:09,810
- Oh please, Sam!

1113
00:56:09,810 --> 00:56:12,120
This is about work.

1114
00:56:12,120 --> 00:56:14,630
I'm behind, and we both
know what that means.

1115
00:56:14,630 --> 00:56:15,880
That there's not much
chance of me bringing

1116
00:56:15,880 --> 00:56:18,003
this project to life. (pants)

1117
00:56:18,003 --> 00:56:20,710
But I wanna have a shot at it.

1118
00:56:20,710 --> 00:56:22,160
So if you'd just let me work.

1119
00:56:23,438 --> 00:56:25,351
Please let me work.

1120
00:56:25,351 --> 00:56:28,268
(thoughtful music)

1121
00:56:48,160 --> 00:56:50,160
- [Janet] What'd I miss?

1122
00:56:51,774 --> 00:56:54,441
(sighs happily)

1123
00:56:56,780 --> 00:57:00,403
- About 18 hours and a mild heart attack,

1124
00:57:03,310 --> 00:57:04,810
but you're gonna be all right.

1125
00:57:06,130 --> 00:57:09,793
No surgery, just a
change in your lifestyle.

1126
00:57:11,850 --> 00:57:14,634
- No more chocolate-chocolate chip?

1127
00:57:14,634 --> 00:57:16,763
- (chuckles) Not after every meal.

1128
00:57:19,340 --> 00:57:20,403
- Heard from Sam?

1129
00:57:21,870 --> 00:57:22,930
(intercom chatters)
- He left a few hours ago.

1130
00:57:22,930 --> 00:57:24,430
He was here most of the night.

1131
00:57:26,320 --> 00:57:29,913
(sighs) He's not having an easy time.

1132
00:57:32,270 --> 00:57:33,653
- Neither did your father.

1133
00:57:35,430 --> 00:57:36,263
- Pardon me?

1134
00:57:38,792 --> 00:57:42,110
- Oh, your father loved me,
in a manner of speaking.

1135
00:57:42,110 --> 00:57:45,193
And he most certainly loved you.

1136
00:57:46,860 --> 00:57:51,860
But he also loved a lady
named Claire, with whom he

1137
00:57:51,920 --> 00:57:56,483
had a somewhat tortured
relationship just under 20 years.

1138
00:57:57,980 --> 00:57:58,813
- What!

1139
00:58:00,720 --> 00:58:05,390
- Claire was married to a prominent judge,

1140
00:58:05,390 --> 00:58:09,623
so she didn't feel she
could get a divorce,

1141
00:58:11,439 --> 00:58:13,533
and I guess your father didn't want one.

1142
00:58:16,573 --> 00:58:17,723
- But you and Dad were always--

1143
00:58:17,723 --> 00:58:20,687
- (groans) Relationships are,

1144
00:58:22,594 --> 00:58:25,303
are just an idea, Elisa.

1145
00:58:27,170 --> 00:58:30,003
Ideas are a function of our imagination.

1146
00:58:31,200 --> 00:58:34,820
You imagined your parents
had a good marriage

1147
00:58:36,140 --> 00:58:37,703
and in many ways, we did.

1148
00:58:39,079 --> 00:58:40,080
- How can you say that if--

1149
00:58:40,080 --> 00:58:45,080
- Oh, I, I had the opportunity
to travel by myself,

1150
00:58:46,070 --> 00:58:47,813
which as you know, I adore.

1151
00:58:49,664 --> 00:58:54,490
And I, I had relationships...

1152
00:58:55,495 --> 00:58:56,395
with other people,

1153
00:58:57,810 --> 00:58:59,393
which I enjoyed as well.

1154
00:59:00,480 --> 00:59:02,980
(Elisa sighs)

1155
00:59:04,000 --> 00:59:06,851
(thoughtful music)

1156
00:59:06,851 --> 00:59:09,684
(papers rustling)

1157
00:59:17,970 --> 00:59:20,150
I can't find the Borowski file!

1158
00:59:20,150 --> 00:59:21,410
Do you have it, Bess?

1159
00:59:21,410 --> 00:59:24,310
- Aha, so there is a correlation

1160
00:59:24,310 --> 00:59:29,130
between sex and organization.
(phone rings)

1161
00:59:29,130 --> 00:59:29,963
Sorry.

1162
00:59:32,610 --> 00:59:34,323
You're gonna get an ulcer, you know?

1163
00:59:35,380 --> 00:59:37,673
Or maybe you'll just go
crazy and kill someone?

1164
00:59:39,153 --> 00:59:40,930
(drawer slams)
- Maybe I'll kill you.

1165
00:59:40,930 --> 00:59:42,600
- Well, at least then
you'll be doing something.

1166
00:59:42,600 --> 00:59:44,620
- I am doing something, Bess.

1167
00:59:44,620 --> 00:59:45,593
- Oh really, what?

1168
00:59:46,910 --> 00:59:48,120
what are you doing?

1169
00:59:48,120 --> 00:59:50,850
You're looking for a file,
you're getting a manicure.

1170
00:59:50,850 --> 00:59:52,740
You're living like your life is normal.

1171
00:59:52,740 --> 00:59:53,760
Like nothing's changed.

1172
00:59:53,760 --> 00:59:55,120
- Fine, Bess, fine!

1173
00:59:55,120 --> 00:59:57,770
I know I should do something,
I just don't know what!

1174
00:59:59,270 --> 01:00:02,800
I played by the rules, we were good!

1175
01:00:02,800 --> 01:00:06,410
We communicated, we fought,
we played, we had a child.

1176
01:00:06,410 --> 01:00:09,743
I enjoyed buying shoes,
clothes, things Sam liked.

1177
01:00:10,798 --> 01:00:11,870
(sighs) There oughta be instructions

1178
01:00:11,870 --> 01:00:14,090
for this because I don't know what to do.

1179
01:00:14,090 --> 01:00:15,560
- Well, maybe that's
because you don't know

1180
01:00:15,560 --> 01:00:18,270
whether you miss Sam or
the life you had with him.

1181
01:00:18,270 --> 01:00:19,770
Well, there's a difference, you know?

1182
01:00:19,770 --> 01:00:20,737
- Stop it, Bess!

1183
01:00:20,737 --> 01:00:22,360
Do you know what I'm doing?

1184
01:00:22,360 --> 01:00:23,830
I'm waking up every morning

1185
01:00:23,830 --> 01:00:26,200
and I am struggling to get out of bed.

1186
01:00:26,200 --> 01:00:28,230
I'm forcing myself to eat a piece of toast

1187
01:00:28,230 --> 01:00:31,020
which nearly gags me, and
then I'm running five miles

1188
01:00:31,020 --> 01:00:32,518
instead of two and a
half because I'm afraid

1189
01:00:32,518 --> 01:00:33,351
if I don't--
- Elisa,

1190
01:00:33,351 --> 01:00:34,360
I didn't mean to upset you like this.

1191
01:00:34,360 --> 01:00:36,560
- Just do me a favor, will you?

1192
01:00:36,560 --> 01:00:40,600
Stop with the ulcer advice
and the dime store psychology.

1193
01:00:40,600 --> 01:00:44,553
And don't you ever, ever use
me to lie to Murray again!

1194
01:00:47,723 --> 01:00:52,306
(sighs)
(slams files)

1195
01:00:56,607 --> 01:00:58,967
(phone rings)
- Mercer Jacobs?

1196
01:00:58,967 --> 01:01:01,967
(employees chatter)

1197
01:01:03,140 --> 01:01:03,973
- Hi, Phyllis.

1198
01:01:05,220 --> 01:01:06,053
- Oh, you can't--

1199
01:01:06,053 --> 01:01:07,303
- I know, he's at the dentist.

1200
01:01:08,350 --> 01:01:10,017
- Phyllis, I'm going to leave--

1201
01:01:12,907 --> 01:01:15,840
(phone rings)

1202
01:01:15,840 --> 01:01:16,673
- You're Nell.

1203
01:01:18,120 --> 01:01:18,953
- Yes, I am.

1204
01:01:20,159 --> 01:01:21,509
I didn't expect to see you.

1205
01:01:23,079 --> 01:01:23,912
- No.

1206
01:01:26,107 --> 01:01:27,310
No, please, don't go.

1207
01:01:27,310 --> 01:01:29,003
Please, just close the door.

1208
01:01:34,342 --> 01:01:36,759
(door thuds)

1209
01:01:40,060 --> 01:01:41,823
- I did not ask Sam to be with me.

1210
01:01:43,320 --> 01:01:45,160
- I asked him not to.

1211
01:01:45,160 --> 01:01:45,993
- Yeah.

1212
01:01:48,500 --> 01:01:51,220
- You know Zoey quit her job
because she couldn't handle

1213
01:01:51,220 --> 01:01:53,360
being here with you and her father?

1214
01:01:53,360 --> 01:01:54,193
- I know.

1215
01:01:57,830 --> 01:01:59,363
- I thought you'd be younger.

1216
01:02:00,769 --> 01:02:03,436
(Nell chuckles)

1217
01:02:05,910 --> 01:02:09,273
- It's a mess, but it's worse for you.

1218
01:02:12,420 --> 01:02:13,620
Because when I'm gone...

1219
01:02:17,400 --> 01:02:18,850
my feelings will be gone too.

1220
01:02:26,280 --> 01:02:27,113
- Nell...

1221
01:02:29,660 --> 01:02:30,493
I'm sorry.

1222
01:02:33,290 --> 01:02:34,390
- Yeah, I'm sorry too.

1223
01:02:36,627 --> 01:02:41,627
(phone rings)
(employees chatter)

1224
01:02:47,100 --> 01:02:49,555
I always preferred salad
at the end of the meal.

1225
01:02:49,555 --> 01:02:50,388
That's they way they do it in Europe.

1226
01:02:50,388 --> 01:02:51,830
- What did you just say?

1227
01:02:51,830 --> 01:02:53,130
- About salad?

1228
01:02:53,130 --> 01:02:53,963
- Before that.

1229
01:02:55,920 --> 01:02:57,170
- About changing my mind?

1230
01:02:58,180 --> 01:02:59,584
Women's prerogative, Sam.

1231
01:02:59,584 --> 01:03:01,184
- (stammers) Cut the crap, Nell.

1232
01:03:02,626 --> 01:03:05,219
Come on, what, what are
you trying to tell me?

1233
01:03:05,219 --> 01:03:07,680
What are you saying?

1234
01:03:07,680 --> 01:03:10,080
- Well, this afternoon I
went to see the doctor.

1235
01:03:12,310 --> 01:03:13,950
I thought I was ready to hear some

1236
01:03:13,950 --> 01:03:16,783
of the less subtle
symptoms of this disease.

1237
01:03:18,080 --> 01:03:19,580
As you know, it can be sudden.

1238
01:03:21,760 --> 01:03:23,470
It all sounds very grim. (sighs)

1239
01:03:23,470 --> 01:03:25,435
- Look Nell, I told you
that doesn't matter to me.

1240
01:03:25,435 --> 01:03:27,230
- It matters to me.

1241
01:03:30,323 --> 01:03:32,740
I think the longer we're together,

1242
01:03:32,740 --> 01:03:35,650
the more difficult it's gonna
be for you when I'm gone.

1243
01:03:35,650 --> 01:03:36,767
- Hey, now, wait a minute.

1244
01:03:36,767 --> 01:03:39,240
Wait, now that's a decision
that I make, not you.

1245
01:03:39,240 --> 01:03:42,203
- No, the dying person
makes the decisions.

1246
01:03:46,729 --> 01:03:49,062
(Sam sighs)

1247
01:03:50,500 --> 01:03:52,050
Your bags are by the door, Sam.

1248
01:03:55,670 --> 01:03:57,220
- Nell, why are you doing this?

1249
01:04:01,740 --> 01:04:04,550
- When I'm with you, I remember I'm dying.

1250
01:04:04,550 --> 01:04:09,493
I feel like I'm dying!
(car alarm blares distantly)

1251
01:04:10,520 --> 01:04:12,070
There's so much anger and pain.

1252
01:04:15,880 --> 01:04:17,700
We started too late, Sam.

1253
01:04:17,700 --> 01:04:19,900
What I have with you,
I do not want to rush.

1254
01:04:20,980 --> 01:04:22,130
Would you please leave?

1255
01:04:24,190 --> 01:04:27,293
Please leave. (gasps softly)

1256
01:04:49,883 --> 01:04:51,810
- Mom, stop if you want to.

1257
01:04:51,810 --> 01:04:52,963
- I'll stop at the car.

1258
01:04:54,091 --> 01:04:55,370
And then, I'm going for a spin.

1259
01:04:55,370 --> 01:04:57,963
- Oh really, who's driving?

1260
01:04:57,963 --> 01:04:59,530
- I've imposed on you long enough.

1261
01:04:59,530 --> 01:05:00,640
And besides, two weeks at your house

1262
01:05:00,640 --> 01:05:02,470
has given me a case of cabin fever.

1263
01:05:02,470 --> 01:05:05,742
- Thank you, it's,
(chuckles) it's been 10 days.

1264
01:05:05,742 --> 01:05:06,740
- Hm.

1265
01:05:06,740 --> 01:05:09,590
- Maybe you'd like to go live
with Sam in his hotel room.

1266
01:05:10,740 --> 01:05:11,890
- He's not with her anymore?

1267
01:05:11,890 --> 01:05:12,940
- I'm not sure.

1268
01:05:12,940 --> 01:05:15,040
He's not staying there, that's all I know.

1269
01:05:16,300 --> 01:05:18,310
Well, here's good news!
(brakes screech)

1270
01:05:18,310 --> 01:05:20,300
Your granddaughter's survived
another wilderness weekend

1271
01:05:20,300 --> 01:05:22,743
with Zack.
(laughing)

1272
01:05:25,797 --> 01:05:27,630
- Uh-oh, looks like trouble in paradise.

1273
01:05:27,630 --> 01:05:29,280
- Maybe it's catching.

1274
01:05:29,280 --> 01:05:31,330
Honey, is something wrong?

1275
01:05:31,330 --> 01:05:33,513
- No, Mom, everything's wrong.

1276
01:05:36,685 --> 01:05:37,518
- Oh, boy.

1277
01:05:41,540 --> 01:05:43,523
- Zack says he doesn't wanna have kids.

1278
01:05:46,040 --> 01:05:49,750
He says they're um, little anchors

1279
01:05:50,890 --> 01:05:55,890
and he wants to sail with the wind.

1280
01:05:56,000 --> 01:05:57,293
- Oh, sweetie.

1281
01:05:59,030 --> 01:06:01,040
- I'm gonna get some honey.

1282
01:06:01,040 --> 01:06:02,550
Does anyone else want honey?

1283
01:06:02,550 --> 01:06:03,383
- No.

1284
01:06:04,469 --> 01:06:05,373
(sighs) Zack.

1285
01:06:06,360 --> 01:06:07,193
- Mom?

1286
01:06:09,538 --> 01:06:10,988
What happened to the kitchen?

1287
01:06:13,890 --> 01:06:14,953
What'd you do?

1288
01:06:17,150 --> 01:06:18,333
- I think your mother
decided that she wanted--

1289
01:06:18,333 --> 01:06:20,610
- I'm making some changes.

1290
01:06:20,610 --> 01:06:22,233
- Some changes?

1291
01:06:23,180 --> 01:06:24,690
Dad built you that kitchen.

1292
01:06:24,690 --> 01:06:26,910
You said that that was
the perfect kitchen!

1293
01:06:26,910 --> 01:06:29,420
- Dad built the kitchen he wanted.

1294
01:06:29,420 --> 01:06:31,343
Now it's gonna be the kitchen I want.

1295
01:06:32,332 --> 01:06:34,140
Okay?
(scoffs)

1296
01:06:34,140 --> 01:06:36,400
- I don't get anyone anymore.

1297
01:06:36,400 --> 01:06:40,943
I mean, you, Zack, Nell, Dad.

1298
01:06:44,240 --> 01:06:46,440
I hope you don't have any
deep, dark secrets, Gran.

1299
01:06:46,440 --> 01:06:47,590
I couldn't handle that.

1300
01:06:52,392 --> 01:06:55,775
- Oh, boy. (slurps tea)

1301
01:06:55,775 --> 01:06:59,775
(crowd talking over each other)

1302
01:07:12,759 --> 01:07:13,592
- I don't see no music room.

1303
01:07:13,592 --> 01:07:15,520
I heard there were gonna be lessons.

1304
01:07:15,520 --> 01:07:16,830
- Yeah, you're gonna
sign up right over there,

1305
01:07:16,830 --> 01:07:18,233
behind the childcare, okay?

1306
01:07:19,190 --> 01:07:20,620
- My momma wants me to play the horn.

1307
01:07:20,620 --> 01:07:22,037
I wanna play the drums.

1308
01:07:24,167 --> 01:07:25,467
- Why don't you play both?

1309
01:07:31,263 --> 01:07:32,850
- Good morning, Sam.
(crowd chatting)

1310
01:07:32,850 --> 01:07:34,186
- Good kid.

1311
01:07:34,186 --> 01:07:35,310
So, how's it going?

1312
01:07:35,310 --> 01:07:37,460
- Good, yeah, people feel good.

1313
01:07:37,460 --> 01:07:38,668
Everybody's helping out.

1314
01:07:38,668 --> 01:07:40,410
- Well good, that's the whole idea.

1315
01:07:40,410 --> 01:07:42,900
- Nell's been working too hard, though.

1316
01:07:42,900 --> 01:07:44,370
- Yeah, I haven't seen too much

1317
01:07:44,370 --> 01:07:45,873
of her the last couple of weeks.

1318
01:07:45,873 --> 01:07:47,580
She's been working at home.

1319
01:07:47,580 --> 01:07:50,413
- Now, what was it she said about you?

1320
01:07:50,413 --> 01:07:51,463
- Oh, brother. (chuckles)

1321
01:07:51,463 --> 01:07:53,693
- That you weren't a diamond in the rough,

1322
01:07:55,376 --> 01:07:57,459
but you were the diamond.

1323
01:07:59,290 --> 01:08:01,537
She said you'd been going
through some tough times,

1324
01:08:01,537 --> 01:08:03,587
that somebody close to you was very sick.

1325
01:08:04,460 --> 01:08:05,293
I'm sorry.

1326
01:08:07,870 --> 01:08:08,920
- This is ridiculous.

1327
01:08:10,276 --> 01:08:11,883
I mean, this is ridiculous!

1328
01:08:17,750 --> 01:08:19,550
If you want, I'll stay at the hotel.

1329
01:08:21,228 --> 01:08:22,061
- No.

1330
01:08:24,800 --> 01:08:25,893
- No to which part?

1331
01:08:29,030 --> 01:08:30,030
- I guess you're um,

1332
01:08:32,551 --> 01:08:35,251
you're lucky that I'm not
strong enough to resist you.

1333
01:08:43,120 --> 01:08:46,037
(thoughtful music)

1334
01:09:00,590 --> 01:09:01,955
Tell me the truth.

1335
01:09:01,955 --> 01:09:02,788
- 'Kay.

1336
01:09:04,290 --> 01:09:05,453
- How do I look?

1337
01:09:09,617 --> 01:09:10,450
- Loved.

1338
01:09:21,120 --> 01:09:22,780
- Okay.
- Okay, now,

1339
01:09:22,780 --> 01:09:24,499
that back splash needs to be light.

1340
01:09:24,499 --> 01:09:25,660
- [Elisa] Right.

1341
01:09:25,660 --> 01:09:28,720
- The 20 years I've been
contracting, people use this.

1342
01:09:28,720 --> 01:09:30,765
Kinda reminds me of an Italian restaurant.

1343
01:09:30,765 --> 01:09:32,371
(laughing)
- Yeah.

1344
01:09:32,371 --> 01:09:34,953
I really, I wanna stick
with these, these are great.

1345
01:09:34,953 --> 01:09:35,786
- Okay.
- Don't you think?

1346
01:09:35,786 --> 01:09:37,510
- Those are nice, yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

1347
01:09:37,510 --> 01:09:38,820
- You might wanna run it
by your husband though,

1348
01:09:38,820 --> 01:09:41,240
'cause couples sometimes get into things

1349
01:09:41,240 --> 01:09:42,210
over this stuff. (chuckles)

1350
01:09:42,210 --> 01:09:44,937
- Mm-hmm, yeah, well I'm separated, so.

1351
01:09:46,580 --> 01:09:47,413
- Oh.

1352
01:09:48,323 --> 01:09:49,460
(door thuds)
- Elisa!

1353
01:09:49,460 --> 01:09:50,330
- Mom!

1354
01:09:50,330 --> 01:09:53,459
Oh Mom, this is my contractor
in here, Richard Pra, uh,

1355
01:09:53,459 --> 01:09:54,292
(stammers) Prinder?

1356
01:09:54,292 --> 01:09:55,125
- Pender.
- Pender, Pender.

1357
01:09:55,125 --> 01:09:55,958
My mother.
- Nice to meet you.

1358
01:09:55,958 --> 01:09:58,160
- Janet Catherine.
- Nice to meet you. (laughs)

1359
01:09:58,160 --> 01:09:59,760
- Why don't I run out and
get those wood samples.

1360
01:09:59,760 --> 01:10:00,593
- Great.

1361
01:10:04,320 --> 01:10:06,310
- Well, it's nice to
have an attractive man

1362
01:10:06,310 --> 01:10:07,160
around the house.

1363
01:10:08,550 --> 01:10:11,390
- I think they gave you too
much oxygen at the hospital.

1364
01:10:11,390 --> 01:10:12,223
- You do?

1365
01:10:13,543 --> 01:10:16,363
I don't.
(birds chirping)

1366
01:10:17,221 --> 01:10:18,900
(papers rustling)
(phone rings)

1367
01:10:18,900 --> 01:10:20,540
- Anyway, the doctors say
she'll have some good days

1368
01:10:20,540 --> 01:10:23,840
but you know, the whole
thing can change overnight.

1369
01:10:23,840 --> 01:10:24,700
From now on, it's all a matter

1370
01:10:24,700 --> 01:10:26,350
of how she feels from day to day.

1371
01:10:27,210 --> 01:10:29,760
- When I ask her how she
feels, she just says fine.

1372
01:10:30,730 --> 01:10:34,280
She used to tell me the truth,
now she just says "fine."

1373
01:10:34,280 --> 01:10:35,113
- Yeah.

1374
01:10:37,344 --> 01:10:39,670
(Zoey knocking)

1375
01:10:39,670 --> 01:10:40,503
Hey!

1376
01:10:40,503 --> 01:10:43,330
- Hi, can I talk to you for a minute?

1377
01:10:43,330 --> 01:10:44,163
- Sure.

1378
01:10:45,080 --> 01:10:47,083
Do me a favor, would you call Nell?

1379
01:10:47,083 --> 01:10:48,090
Tell her I'll be a few minutes late

1380
01:10:48,090 --> 01:10:50,150
and ask her if there's anything
else she needs, all right?

1381
01:10:50,150 --> 01:10:50,983
- You got it.

1382
01:11:10,370 --> 01:11:11,560
- What I wanna know...

1383
01:11:14,430 --> 01:11:17,130
is how come you still have
Mom's picture on your desk?

1384
01:11:19,640 --> 01:11:23,563
- Because she's my
wife, and I, I love her.

1385
01:11:25,580 --> 01:11:28,810
- Right, I...

1386
01:11:30,566 --> 01:11:32,130
(inhales) I don't get it.

1387
01:11:32,130 --> 01:11:34,727
- Oh (sighs) Zoey, I'm
not sure I do either.

1388
01:11:36,703 --> 01:11:38,823
Relationships are never airtight.

1389
01:11:39,920 --> 01:11:40,933
They, they have,

1390
01:11:43,050 --> 01:11:44,173
empty spaces.

1391
01:11:46,640 --> 01:11:48,577
And when things are mostly good,

1392
01:11:48,577 --> 01:11:51,400
well you, you just
don't notice the spaces,

1393
01:11:51,400 --> 01:11:52,963
but then something happens.

1394
01:11:56,430 --> 01:12:01,430
And someone comes along and
she fills up those spaces.

1395
01:12:03,081 --> 01:12:05,970
(stammers) She makes you realize

1396
01:12:05,970 --> 01:12:09,543
that they were there in
the first place and how,

1397
01:12:11,760 --> 01:12:16,760
how wonderful it feels not
to have them empty anymore.

1398
01:12:27,086 --> 01:12:28,736
(sighs) So what about your plans?

1399
01:12:30,540 --> 01:12:31,380
- Oh, um...

1400
01:12:33,180 --> 01:12:35,280
Well, (stammers) we postponed the wedding.

1401
01:12:36,360 --> 01:12:41,360
Um, Zack and I are reviewing
some things and besides,

1402
01:12:42,700 --> 01:12:46,563
the original date didn't
work with um, Mom's new job.

1403
01:12:48,910 --> 01:12:49,743
- Your mom has a job?

1404
01:12:49,743 --> 01:12:52,500
- Oh yeah, the one they always
wanted her for at the museum.

1405
01:12:58,532 --> 01:13:02,111
You should see what she's
done to the kitchen.

1406
01:13:02,111 --> 01:13:02,973
And the backyard.

1407
01:13:07,321 --> 01:13:09,654
(bird caws)

1408
01:13:11,565 --> 01:13:14,573
(dog barks)

1409
01:13:14,573 --> 01:13:15,934
(Elisa gasps)

1410
01:13:15,934 --> 01:13:18,833
- (sighs) You scared me!

1411
01:13:18,833 --> 01:13:20,410
- I'm sorry.

1412
01:13:20,410 --> 01:13:22,390
What are you doing, Elisa?

1413
01:13:22,390 --> 01:13:24,540
- I'm having a new
sprinkler system put in.

1414
01:13:26,060 --> 01:13:27,110
- That's a good idea.

1415
01:13:28,040 --> 01:13:29,190
- I'm glad you approve.

1416
01:13:30,350 --> 01:13:33,073
- So, Zoey said that
you'd taken a new job.

1417
01:13:34,000 --> 01:13:34,833
- Yes, I did.

1418
01:13:37,606 --> 01:13:39,303
- You know, you don't need to do that.

1419
01:13:41,770 --> 01:13:42,603
Elisa?

1420
01:13:51,231 --> 01:13:52,931
(door thuds)
- You want some tea?

1421
01:13:53,830 --> 01:13:55,873
- Yeah, herbal if you have it.

1422
01:14:01,107 --> 01:14:04,943
Elisa, (scoffs) I thought
you loved this kitchen.

1423
01:14:06,370 --> 01:14:10,560
- Yeah, I thought so too, huh.

1424
01:14:10,560 --> 01:14:12,070
You know, after we were married,

1425
01:14:12,070 --> 01:14:15,030
I felt so fulfilled and happy, you know?

1426
01:14:15,030 --> 01:14:17,390
And then we had Zoey, and
I even felt more fulfilled,

1427
01:14:17,390 --> 01:14:19,090
which I didn't think was possible.

1428
01:14:20,160 --> 01:14:22,810
I didn't give a lot of
thought to what else I wanted.

1429
01:14:25,890 --> 01:14:28,053
Did you know my father had a mistress?

1430
01:14:30,924 --> 01:14:32,286
- No.

1431
01:14:32,286 --> 01:14:34,869
(Elisa scoffs)

1432
01:14:37,180 --> 01:14:39,263
- You know, you really
scared me out there.

1433
01:14:40,759 --> 01:14:41,700
- I'm sorry, I didn't mean to.

1434
01:14:41,700 --> 01:14:43,400
- I think I'd like your house key.

1435
01:14:46,708 --> 01:14:49,875
(dog barks distantly)

1436
01:14:52,528 --> 01:14:57,528
(kids screaming)
(whimsical music)

1437
01:14:58,530 --> 01:15:01,011
- Sweetie, it's an awful night.

1438
01:15:01,011 --> 01:15:01,844
Why don't we just go home?

1439
01:15:01,844 --> 01:15:03,763
- (sighs) No, Sam, I love the rain.

1440
01:15:06,920 --> 01:15:09,150
You think people can tell?

1441
01:15:09,150 --> 01:15:10,527
- About your being sick?

1442
01:15:10,527 --> 01:15:12,333
- No, about how much I love you.

1443
01:15:16,464 --> 01:15:20,520
- Would you mind if I asked
you a very personal question?

1444
01:15:20,520 --> 01:15:21,353
- Sure.

1445
01:15:22,770 --> 01:15:23,820
- Would you marry me?

1446
01:15:25,064 --> 01:15:28,481
(thoughtful piano music)

1447
01:15:31,025 --> 01:15:31,858
Hm?

1448
01:15:32,980 --> 01:15:35,217
- If I live long enough
to write my memoirs...

1449
01:15:38,710 --> 01:15:40,660
this night will definitely be in there.

1450
01:15:42,480 --> 01:15:43,573
A man proposed.

1451
01:15:46,200 --> 01:15:48,417
I said, "No."

1452
01:15:51,280 --> 01:15:52,580
That I needed to throw up.

1453
01:15:54,720 --> 01:15:56,772
I saw a restroom somewhere up here.

1454
01:15:56,772 --> 01:15:58,555
- Come on, come on.

1455
01:15:58,555 --> 01:16:01,472
(thoughtful music)

1456
01:16:08,306 --> 01:16:12,560
- Maybe we should tell the
doctor about our sex therapy.

1457
01:16:12,560 --> 01:16:14,665
'Course, he might think
that you were a pervert.

1458
01:16:14,665 --> 01:16:17,037
- Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, I love you too.

1459
01:16:18,657 --> 01:16:21,257
- And he couldn't possibly
imagine so much pleasure.

1460
01:16:26,187 --> 01:16:28,770
(rain patters)

1461
01:16:48,528 --> 01:16:49,372
- Woo!

1462
01:16:49,372 --> 01:16:50,851
I'm back.
(door slams)

1463
01:16:50,851 --> 01:16:52,923
It's showtime, comedy night!

1464
01:16:53,800 --> 01:16:57,377
I got "Spaceballs," I got "Naked Gun."

1465
01:16:58,400 --> 01:17:00,020
I got "The Twelve Chairs,"
I betcha there's--

1466
01:17:00,020 --> 01:17:00,853
- Sam.

1467
01:17:02,180 --> 01:17:03,380
The doctor's on his way.

1468
01:17:06,645 --> 01:17:08,663
(bag thuds)

1469
01:17:08,663 --> 01:17:10,746
- I was gone for an hour.

1470
01:17:13,579 --> 01:17:16,662
(Nell groans weakly)

1471
01:17:25,807 --> 01:17:26,930
(Sam murmurs)

1472
01:17:26,930 --> 01:17:27,763
- Thank God.

1473
01:17:29,210 --> 01:17:30,113
- Listen to me.

1474
01:17:32,810 --> 01:17:36,090
See, see, the only problem
at the carnival was

1475
01:17:36,090 --> 01:17:38,667
that I wasn't prepared.

1476
01:17:38,667 --> 01:17:40,167
- Prepared?
- Yeah.

1477
01:17:43,514 --> 01:17:46,279
(wistful music)

1478
01:17:46,279 --> 01:17:50,862
Nell Bergen, would you do me
the very great honor of...

1479
01:17:54,847 --> 01:17:59,729
becoming my wife?
(rain patters)

1480
01:17:59,729 --> 01:18:02,979
(Nell breathes weakly)

1481
01:18:03,977 --> 01:18:06,265
- Can I tell you a secret?

1482
01:18:06,265 --> 01:18:07,098
- Sure.

1483
01:18:09,457 --> 01:18:11,290
- When I was little...

1484
01:18:13,729 --> 01:18:16,979
people asked me, what did I want to be?

1485
01:18:22,599 --> 01:18:24,373
I said, "Engaged.

1486
01:18:27,844 --> 01:18:30,261
Never married, just engaged."

1487
01:18:31,751 --> 01:18:34,168
(Sam sniffs)

1488
01:18:35,653 --> 01:18:38,205
(Sam chuckles)

1489
01:18:38,205 --> 01:18:42,308
Sam, I don't know what it was between us.

1490
01:18:42,308 --> 01:18:47,308
- Is, hon, what it is. (kisses)

1491
01:18:49,350 --> 01:18:52,260
- Sometimes, people just fit.

1492
01:18:52,260 --> 01:18:55,177
(melancholy music)

1493
01:19:00,804 --> 01:19:01,637
Sam...

1494
01:19:06,832 --> 01:19:09,082
I want you to let go of me.

1495
01:19:11,796 --> 01:19:13,273
- Oh, no, no, no, no, no. (whispers)

1496
01:19:13,273 --> 01:19:14,900
Just rest, the doctor's on his way.

1497
01:19:14,900 --> 01:19:16,650
- I'm not engaged to the doctor.

1498
01:19:22,239 --> 01:19:24,527
I need you to let go.

1499
01:19:24,527 --> 01:19:26,860
- [Sam] No, no, not yet, no.

1500
01:19:27,823 --> 01:19:29,957
Not yet, please, not yet.

1501
01:19:29,957 --> 01:19:32,624
I, I, I want, I want more, Nell.

1502
01:19:34,557 --> 01:19:37,018
Nell, please, please.

1503
01:19:37,018 --> 01:19:39,503
(Nell breathes weakly)

1504
01:19:39,503 --> 01:19:40,420
Nell, Nell?

1505
01:19:41,567 --> 01:19:43,734
Nell, come on, Nell, Nell.

1506
01:19:46,445 --> 01:19:48,124
(music swells)
(stammering)

1507
01:19:48,124 --> 01:19:49,624
I need more, Nell.

1508
01:19:51,526 --> 01:19:54,026
(sobs softly)

1509
01:20:15,547 --> 01:20:18,464
(melancholy music)

1510
01:20:46,370 --> 01:20:48,870
(phone rings)

1511
01:20:50,136 --> 01:20:51,620
(Zoey knocking)

1512
01:20:51,620 --> 01:20:52,453
- Yeah?

1513
01:20:54,794 --> 01:20:55,979
- Got a minute?

1514
01:20:55,979 --> 01:20:56,812
- Hey. (chuckles)

1515
01:20:56,812 --> 01:20:58,093
For you, I got more than that.

1516
01:21:00,778 --> 01:21:02,133
So, what's up?

1517
01:21:03,610 --> 01:21:05,063
- I'm going to Europe.

1518
01:21:05,987 --> 01:21:07,973
- (laughs) Didn't I know this already?

1519
01:21:09,610 --> 01:21:11,400
- Not with Zack.

1520
01:21:11,400 --> 01:21:12,630
- Oh.

1521
01:21:12,630 --> 01:21:13,830
- With my friend, Lydia.

1522
01:21:15,060 --> 01:21:15,893
- Ah.

1523
01:21:18,000 --> 01:21:21,940
- The relationship thing is weird.

1524
01:21:21,940 --> 01:21:22,890
- Tell me about it.

1525
01:21:23,740 --> 01:21:25,820
- Um, Dad.

1526
01:21:25,820 --> 01:21:26,653
- Yeah?

1527
01:21:27,900 --> 01:21:29,450
- I wanted you to know...

1528
01:21:31,520 --> 01:21:32,770
I would have invited you

1529
01:21:34,110 --> 01:21:36,327
to the wedding if there had been one.

1530
01:21:37,600 --> 01:21:39,300
I would have invited you and Nell.

1531
01:21:41,387 --> 01:21:44,575
- Oh sweetie, thanks.

1532
01:21:44,575 --> 01:21:46,275
(stammers) That means a lot to me.

1533
01:21:53,038 --> 01:21:54,020
